						<summary>

						<p>Records that the members of the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Śrīraṅgam agreed to run the service of burning a lamp in front of Tiruvaraṅgattu-Perumāṉaḍigaḷ with <hi rend="italic">Bhīmasēṉi-kaṟpūram</hi> (camphor) and ghee provided for, from the interest on 71 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold invested by Śrīdharaṉ Kumaraṉ, a <hi rend="italic">Malaiyāḷaṉ</hi> of Iravimaṅgalam in Vaḷḷuva-nāḍu of Malai-nāḍu. The record is dated in the fifteenth regnal year of <hi rend="bold">Uttama Chōḷa.</hi> cf. No. 4 above.</p>						

						</summary>
